  ANIMALS OF THE WORLD
============================================================

Name:         Saltwater Crocodile
Scientific:   Crocodylus porosus
Class:        Reptilia
Habitat:      Coastal
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     70 years
Weight:       1000 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Strongest bite force of any living animal; survived dinosaurs

Name:         Mimic Octopus
Scientific:   Thaumoctopus mimicus
Class:        Cephalopoda
Habitat:      Shallow sea
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     1 years
Weight:       0.5 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Can mimic 15+ different species including lionfish and flatfish

Name:         Giant Panda
Scientific:   Ailuropoda melanoleuca
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Temperate forest
Diet:         Herbivore
Lifespan:     20 years
Weight:       100 kg
Status:       Vulnerable
Fact:         Eats 12-38 kg bamboo daily; has a sixth finger (pseudo-thumb)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Maximize pleasure minimize pain across all sentient beings
Philosopher:  Jeremy Bentham
Example:      Felicific calculus: measure units of pleasure and pain

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

